webpackJsonp([0xfb3dc26d5fd8],{6773:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{post:{html:'<p>It worked! :-) At least 95% worked, and the few problems could be easily fixed. Two notes:</p>\n<p>1. We decided to skip domain mapping, since we don\'t have a group for all Samba users, and Samba 3 only maps one-to-one. </p>\n<p>2. To convert the SIDs, I exported the smbpasswd to XML, added line breaks, ran this perl script, and imported into samtdb.</p>\n<p>:<br />\n    #!/usr/bin/perl<br />\n    while (<>) {<br />\n        if (/sid=/) {<br />\n                /-(d+)"/;<br />\n                my $oldrid=$1;<br />\n                my $newrid= (($oldrid-1000)*2)+1000 ;<br />\n                s/-d+"/-$newrid"/;<br />\n        }<br />\n        print;<br />\n    }</p>',fields:{title:"Samba 3... yes!",date:"07 Apr 2004",url:"https://papascott.de/2004-04-07-samba-3-yes/"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/2004-04-07-samba-3-yes/",prev:{fields:{title:"Smarty Templates and Movable Type",date:"06 Apr 2004",slug:"/2004-04-06-smarty-templates-and-movable-type/"}},next:{fields:{title:"Crossroads",date:"08 Apr 2004",slug:"/2004-04-08-crossroads/"}}}}}});
